$ Excel: active cell
@ active cell

There is always *one* active cell in each → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window[window], even if the current selection contains multiple cells.
-
The active cell is the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/cell where data entered by a user goes to.

gh|about-Excel|/GUI/selection/only-one-active-cell.png||

The keyboard shortcut key `F2` allows to edit the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/formulas of the active cell.
-
Within a selection, the active cell can be moved with `tab`, `enter`, `shift+tab` and `shift+enter`.

sa:
  The currently → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/cell/active can be found with → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application#excel-application-active-objects[`application.activeCell`].

  `→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application[application].moveAfterReturn` controls if the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/cell/active is moved when the Enter key is pressed. If `true`, it moves to the direction specified in `application.moveAfterReturnDirection`

